div.p:
“I am a merchant from a far country,” said the man;

“many wonderful things do I bring to your emperor, if he

will purchase of my valuables.”

Placid to men and to immortal gods;
Mild from the first beginning of her days;
Gentlest of all in Heaven.

He has also nearly ready for the press, Bibliotheca Americana Vetus : a

Catalogue of Books relating to America from the Discovery to the year 1700;

with notes and observations: in one volume, 8vo., of about 400 pages.
